Argentine Stock Movers: Banco Macro, Galicia, Ledesma, Petrobras

-- B y   C a m i l a   R u s s o
-- 
2011-09-02T21:00:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-02/argentine-stock-movers-banco-macro-galicia-ledesma-saai.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Argentine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 4 p.m.  New York  time.  The Merval Index fell 1.9 percent to 2,872.11.  Banks fell after hiring in the U.S. unexpectedly stagnated
last month, fueling concern global growth may slow.  Banco Macro SA (BMA)  ,  Argentina ’s largest lender by
market value, dropped 3.4 percent to 11.40 pesos.    Grupo Financiero Galicia SA (GGAL)  , Argentina’s largest
consumer lender, plunged 2.7 percent to 5.03 pesos  Ledesma SAAI (LEDE AF), the Argentine sugar producer,
tumbled 1.8 percent to 7.50 pesos. Raw sugar for October
delivery declined 1.4 percent to 29.18 cents a pound on ICE
Futures U.S. in New York.  Petroleo Brasileiro SA (PETR4)   lost 3.6 percent to 61
pesos. Crude prices dropped on concern that fuel consumption
will decline in the world’s largest economy.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Camila Russo in  Buenos Aires  at 
 crusso15@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
